SIMPLE: lineal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lineal
<hw>Lin"e*al</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>linealis</ets> belonging to a line, fr. <ets>linea</ets>
line: cf. F. <ets>lin⟦eacute⟧al</ets>. See 3d <er>Line</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Descending in a direct line from an ancestor;
hereditary; derived from ancestors; -- opposed to
<contr>collateral</contr>; <as>as, a <ex>lineal</ex> descent or a
<ex>lineal</ex> descendant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The prime and ancient right of <qex>lineal</qex> succession.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inheriting by direct descent; having the right by
direct descent to succeed (<ptcl>to</ptcl>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For only you are <qex>lineal</qex> to the throne.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Composed of lines; delineated; <as>as,
<ex>lineal</ex> designs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>In the direction of a line; of or pertaining to a
line; measured on, or ascertained by, a line; linear; <as>as,
<ex>lineal</ex> magnitude</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lineal measure</b></col>, <cd>the measure of length; --
usually written <altname>linear measure</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lineality</ent>⟦br⟧
